<paragraph blockId="5.[2083,2676,2379,2801]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2083,2238,2379,2408]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Thomas" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1901" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Heteromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">Heteromys australis Thomas, 1901</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation pageId="5" pageNumber="198">“St. Javier, Lower Cachabi River, N. Ecuador. Alt. 20 m.”</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[2083,2676,2379,2801]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">
With the exception of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1868" box="[2434,2676,2497,2526]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Heteromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="desmarestianus">H. desmarestianus</taxonomicName>
in the north-western corner of Colombia, the South American spiny pocket mice all belong to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thompson" authorityYear="1815" box="[2337,2461,2611,2644]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Heteromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="anomalus">anomalus</taxonomicName>
species group: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thompson" authorityYear="1815" box="[2085,2266,2659,2686]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Heteromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="anomalus">H. anomalus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Anderson &amp; Gutierrez" authorityYear="2009" box="[2298,2490,2659,2686]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Heteromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="catopterius">H. catopterius</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Anderson" authorityYear="2003" box="[2521,2668,2659,2684]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Heteromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oasicus">H. oasicus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1901" box="[2084,2237,2698,2723]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Heteromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">H. australis</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="R. P. Anderson &amp; Jarrin-Valladares" authorityYear="2002" box="[2318,2430,2698,2723]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Heteromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="teleus">H. teleus</taxonomicName>
. Only 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1901" box="[2523,2676,2698,2723]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Heteromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">H. australis</taxonomicName>
exists outside of South America in eastern Panama. Three subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
